# Cursor rules — CSA Loom Azure-native client patterns
# (mirror of AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md for Cursor; full detail in skills/<name>/SKILL.md)

CSA Loom has NO hard dependency on real Microsoft Fabric or Power BI. Every item
type works 100% on Azure-native backends BY DEFAULT. When generating or editing
CSA Loom code:

- Call the Azure-native client, NEVER api.fabric.microsoft.com / api.powerbi.com /
  onelake.dfs.fabric.microsoft.com on the default path. Fabric is opt-in only
  (LOOM_<ITEM>_BACKEND=fabric + a bound workspace).
- Do not gate a feature on fabricWorkspaceId without an Azure-native fallback in
  the same function.

Item -> Azure-native backend -> client (under apps/fiab-console/lib/azure/):
- lakehouse            -> ADLS Gen2 + Delta            -> adls-client.ts, synapse-sql-client.ts   (/api/lakehouse, /api/onelake)
- warehouse            -> Synapse dedicated SQL pool   -> synapse-sql-client.ts, synapse-pool-arm.ts (/api/warehouse)
- kql-database         -> Azure Data Explorer (ADX)    -> kusto-client.ts, kusto-arm-client.ts     (/api/adx)
- eventstream          -> Azure Event Hubs             -> eventhubs-client.ts, stream-analytics-client.ts (/api/eventhubs)
- data-pipeline        -> Synapse pipeline / ADF       -> synapse-dev-client.ts, adf-client.ts     (/api/adf)
- activator            -> Azure Monitor alert          -> monitor-client.ts                        (/api/monitor)
- mirrored-database    -> ADF CDC -> ADLS Delta        -> adf-client.ts, mirror-engine.ts          (/api/items)
- semantic-model/report-> Loom-native over Synapse/AAS -> aas-client.ts, paginated-report-client.ts (/api/powerbi)
- search/catalog       -> Azure AI Search + Cosmos     -> loom-search.ts, loom-docs-index.ts       (/api/ai-search)

Hosts differ per sovereign cloud (Commercial / GCC / GCC-High / DoD). NEVER
hard-code management.azure.com / kusto.windows.net / dfs.core.windows.net.
Derive every host from apps/fiab-console/lib/azure/cloud-endpoints.ts helpers
(armBase(), kustoSuffix(), dfsSuffix(), getGraphHost()) keyed off detectLoomCloud().

Auth: ChainedTokenCredential(ManagedIdentityCredential({clientId: LOOM_UAMI_CLIENT_ID}),
DefaultAzureCredential()) with per-resource .default scopes from cloud-endpoints.

BFF routes return { ok: true, data } | { ok: false, error, code? } with a real
HTTP status. Missing infra -> honest config gate (HTTP 503, code:'not_configured'),
never a mock array / return [] / hard-coded sample data.

See README.md and skills/<name>/SKILL.md for full patterns.
